The paper deals with cyber-attacks and their prediction, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of recommender systems for predicting future attacks involves machine learning techniques, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the analysis of data from the maritime supply chain infrastructure, which can be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a method for risk management, which can be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE).
